## Current Blue Nile Inventory: How to Filter for Fluorescence

On Blue Nile's advanced diamond search:

1. Apply the full proportion filter: GIA, Cut = Excellent, Table 54–57%, Depth 59–62.3%, Crown Angle 34–35°, Pavilion Angle 40.6–41.0°
2. Under "Fluorescence," select the grade(s) you want to include: typically None + Faint for zero-risk, or add Medium/Strong for discount hunting
3. Sort by price per carat (ascending)
4. The lowest-priced stones in the filtered results with Strong or Very Strong fluorescence are your discount candidates
5. Watch the 360° video for every fluorescence candidate before purchasing

Key reference stones with confirmed None fluorescence (zero risk baseline):
- [GIA 1.00 Carat G-VS2 Excellent Cut Round Diamond](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/29090690?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) — $3,230
